H2.text: Who made the 1995 album 'Jagged Little Pill' which sold 33 million copies. Sarah McLachlan

H3.text: Who made the 1995 album 'Jagged Little Pill' which sold 33 million copies. Alanis

A4.text: After relocating to Los Angeles, she released the alternative rock album Jagged Little Pill (1995), which became one of the best-selling albums of all time and has appeared on several all-time lists.

A5.text: Jagged Little Pill sold more than 16 million copies in the U.S.; it sold 33 million worldwide, making it the second biggest-selling album by a female artist (behind Shania Twain's Come On Over).
